The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, June 15, 2003 				 Cong bandh
 Behrampore, June 14: The  district Congress has called a 12-hour bandh on June 20  to protest against the state health departments inefficiency  in tackling the spate of infant deaths in the region, reports  our correspondent. Over 40 children have died in the last  20 days after a mystery fever rocked the district several  sub-divisions when a mystery fever killed over 40 children. District Congress chief, Adhir  Chowdhury, said here today that the manner in which the  health officials had not given any importance to the outbreak.  The health department has not done anything to haul up  the guilty doctors on duty, Chowdhury said. The state health  department had issued a show-cause notice to the additional  chief medical officer of the district following the deaths.
